The paper deals with game theory and algorithms for finding equilibria, which are topics commonly found in the cs.GT (Game Theory) sub-category. The use of path-following algorithms and polynomial time solutions suggest a focus on computational complexity, which could place the paper in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-categories. The mention of finding equilibria using AI techniques could also suggest a connection to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of a rank-preserving homeomorphism could suggest a connection to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category, which often deals with network structures and their properties.
